    "recap_headline": "West Virginia University",
    "recap_text": "MORGANTOWN, W.Va.\u00a0\u2013\u00a0The No. 20 West Virginia University baseball team came back from five runs down against BYU to win 12-10, Friday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 15-4 overall and 4-1 in the Big 12 while the Cougars fall to 10-11 and 2-3 in league play.\nSenior\nPaul Schoenfeld\nhad a big day at the plate, going 5-for-5 with two doubles, two RBI, and two runs, and has now reached base in 10 straight plate appearances. Sophomore\nGavin Kelly\nhad three hits and three RBI while graduate student\nBrodie Kresser\nhad two hits and three RBI. Overall, WVU collected 18 hits in the game.\nGraduate student\nIan Korn\nearned his first win as a Mountaineer with 4.2 innings in relief, allowing two runs and striking out a season-high seven batters. Freshman\nDavid Perez\nearned his second save of the series and fourth of the season.\nThe two teams traded runs in the second before BYU put up a three-spot in the third after a brief rain delay. In the home half of the third, West Virginia got back within one as Kelly had an RBI double and Schoenfeld an RBI single.\nThe Cougars took their biggest lead of the game with four runs in the fourth. Once again, the Mountaineers got back within one with four runs of their own in the fifth inning. A two-run single from Kresser opened the scoring before an error opened the door for two more runs. Kresser then tied the game in the sixth on a sacrifice fly.\nIn the seventh, WVU tallied its second four-run inning of the game, this time beginning with two outs and nobody on. Junior\nTyrus Hall\nstarted with a single before sophomore\nMatt Ineich\nworked a walk. Kelly followed with a two-run triple to put the Mountaineers in front. Schoenfeld then drove in Kelly with his fifth hit of the game before coming around to score on a wild pitch.\nBYU hit a two-run home run in the ninth before Perez came in and shut the door.\nWest Virginia will look for its second sweep of the season tomorrow afternoon with first pitch set for 12:30 p.m.\nFor more information on the Mountaineers, follow @WVUBaseball on\nTwitter\n,\nFacebook\n, and\nInstagram\n.",
